cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.SE, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an unsupervised load disaggregation approach that learns and updates the number of used appliances and their corresponding models in operation. This involves machine learning techniques such as clustering and feature extraction.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed algorithm works autonomously in real time, which involves artificial intelligence techniques such as decision making and control.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper describes the implementation of the proposed algorithm and its evaluation on real world data, which involves software engineering techniques such as programming and testing.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a novel approach for load disaggregation, which involves software engineering techniques such as design and development.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The proposed algorithm tries to detect power states corresponding to on/off appliances as well as to multi-state appliances based on active power measurements in 1s resolution, which involves systems and control techniques such as signal processing and estimation.
